cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper presents a new scheme for learning graph-structured data based on hyperbolic embedding, Riemannian barycentre, and K-means algorithms. This work involves machine learning, artificial intelligence, and data science, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.DS. The paper also deals with social networks and hierarchical graph-structured data, which are related to the sub-categories cs.SI and cs.NE.
